  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2.48.0-stable-084acc1a`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: `Alpine Linux v3.17` (Kubernetes (GKE) running image https://hub.docker.com/r/thorax/erigon) \r\n96GB RAM\r\n4 CPUs\r\n10 TB SSD (in Kubernetes so the IOPS is not optimal I guess)\r\n\r\nCommit hash: `git_branch=heads/v2.48.0 git_tag=v2.48.0-dirty git_commit=084acc1af2e853ee4a57dbdd6920b6a1e58ef85c`\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n```\r\nerigon --chain=bor-mainnet --datadir=/data/ --bor.heimdall=http://heimdallrest --authrpc.vhosts=heimdallrest --authrpc.jwtsecret=/secret/jwt.hex --db.size.limit=8TB --maxpeers=500 --torrent.download.rate=300mb --h\r\nttp --ws --http.api=eth,admin,debug,net,trace,web3,erigon,txpool --authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer:\r\nHeimdall\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer Command (with flags/config):\r\n`heimdalld start --home=/heimdall-home`\r\n\r\nChain/Network: \r\nBor-Mainnet\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAt least when a sync stage X/15 reports DONE, the sync progress is restarted from the last finished stage after a reboot.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAfter the reboot in sync stage 12/15 and after over 200 hours of sync time Erigon begins syncing again from the previous downloaded snapshot from 23th of may 2023.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nReboot Erigon after one of the first 11 finished sync stages. \r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nJust the logs where you can see the reboot and then beginning the sync again from the start.\r\n````\r\n[INFO] [07-24|13:14:08.225] [txpool] stat                            pending=10000 baseFee=30000 queued=30000 alloc=9.6GB sys=17.3GB\r\n[INFO] [07-24|13:14:11.087] [12/15 StorageHistoryIndex] ETL [2/2] Loading into=StorageHistory current_prefix=2ab0e9e4\r\n[INFO] [07-24|13:14:34.063] [12/15 StorageHistoryIndex] ETL [2/2] Loading into=StorageHistory current_prefix=2ab0e9e4\r\n[INFO] [07-24|13:15:04.062] [12/15 StorageHistoryIndex] ETL [2/2] Lo