    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "It's trade-off between: \"show only fully-indexed data\" VS \"commit partial progress\"\r\nat initial-sync we choose commit partial data (non-indexed data are visible by RPC), but then we switch to show only consistent data (indexed, etc...) - commit all stages at once. \r\n\r\ncurrent logic is here: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/521f0df55b6a44ed322b417cc6cf93b92060a947/turbo/stages/stageloop.go#L111 - if you see better idea/logic - feel free to advise\r\n\r\n\r\n",
